      "description": "Three-loop ice cone graph with equal internal masses. The geometry involves two distinct elliptic curves, both related to the equal-mass two-loop sunrise curve evaluated at $z$ and $1/z$. Reparametrized via Landau variable $s=-(1-z)^2/z$. 8 master integrals. A new function $G$ coupling the two elliptic sectors is introduced. The maximal cut system factorizes into two $2 \\times 2$ sunrise-type blocks. The epsilon-factorised GM connection involves the holomorphic periods of both elliptic curves and the coupling function $G$.",
